               <msContents>
                  <summary>List of donkey drivers with the number of donkeys supplied by each man as he transported state grain; the names of the drivers are arranged by groups according to village</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Written along the fibers; on the back P.Col. V verso 5</note>
                     <note type="general">4 cols. of writing; 27 lines in col. 1; 30 in col. 2; 25 lines in col. 3; and 15 in col. 4</note>
                     <note type="general">Large blank space underneath the last col</note>
                     <note type="general">The list is a record of grain transport by land from a granary to the harbor</note>
                     <note type="general">These donkey (and camel) drivers were "public" in the sense that they had to keep 3 donkeys ready for state service of transportation</note>
